sequenceDiagram
    participant MM as ModelMesh Serving
    participant KS as KServe InferenceLogger
    participant TrustyAI as TrustyAI Service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant Reconciler as Payload Reconciler<br/>(in-memory ID matching)
    participant Storage as Storage Backend<br/>(PVC/MinIO/MariaDB)
    participant Scheduler as PrometheusScheduler<br/>(periodic, default 5s)
    participant Publisher as PrometheusPublisher<br/>(Micrometer gauges)
    participant Prom as Prometheus<br/>OpenShift Monitoring
    participant Client as Client / Dashboard
    participant ModelServer as KServe Model Server

    Note over MM, Storage: Flow 1: ModelMesh Inference Payload Reconciliation
    MM->>TrustyAI: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>Base64-encoded protobuf payload<br/>80/TCP HTTP, no auth
    TrustyAI->>Reconciler: Decode protobuf, extract inference ID
    Note right of Reconciler: Matches input/output pairs<br/>by inference ID (synchronized)
    Reconciler->>Storage: Persist reconciled Dataframe row

    Note over KS, Storage: Flow 2: KServe Inference Payload Reconciliation
    KS->>TrustyAI: CloudEvent (Knative Funqy)<br/>JSON inference payload<br/>80/TCP HTTP, no auth
    TrustyAI->>Reconciler: Parse CloudEvent, extract inference ID
    Note right of Reconciler: ID-based matching<br/>(input + output pairing)
    Reconciler->>Storage: Persist reconciled Dataframe row

    Note over Scheduler, Prom: Flow 3: Scheduled Metric Computation
    loop Every 5 seconds (configurable)
        Scheduler->>Storage: Read latest data batch<br/>(batch_size: 50000)
        Storage-->>Scheduler: Dataframe rows
        Scheduler->>Scheduler: Compute SPD, DIR,<br/>Meanshift, FourierMMD
        Scheduler->>Publisher: Update Micrometer gauges<br/>(trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir, ...)
    end
    Prom->>TrustyAI: GET /q/metrics<br/>80/TCP HTTP<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (SA)
    TrustyAI-->>Prom: Prometheus gauge values

    Note over Client, ModelServer: Flow 4: On-Demand Explainability (disabled in RHOAI)
    Client->>TrustyAI: POST /explainers/local/lime<br/>80/TCP HTTP, no auth
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Read prediction data
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Historical predictions
    TrustyAI->>ModelServer: gRPC ModelInfer (v2 protocol)<br/>Perturbed inputs, plaintext
    ModelServer-->>TrustyAI: Inference results
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute LIME explanation
    TrustyAI-->>Client: JSON explanation response

    Note over Client, TrustyAI: Flow 5: On-Demand Fairness Metric
    Client->>TrustyAI: POST /metrics/group/fairness/spd<br/>80/TCP HTTP, no auth
    TrustyAI->>Storage: Read data for model
    Storage-->>TrustyAI: Dataframe
    TrustyAI->>TrustyAI: Compute SPD metric
    TrustyAI-->>Client: JSON metric result

    Note over Client, TrustyAI: Flow 6: Schedule Recurring Metric
    Client->>TrustyAI: POST /metrics/group/fairness/spd/request<br/>80/TCP HTTP, no auth
    TrustyAI->>Scheduler: Register periodic SPD computation
    TrustyAI-->>Client: 200 OK (schedule created)
    Note right of Scheduler: Metric now computed on<br/>each scheduler tick and<br/>published to Prometheus
